cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic results in a model of self-assembly, which involves combinatorial and geometric aspects. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which covers topics such as combinatorics, graph theory, and discrete optimization. The paper also involves computational complexity, as it discusses the computational power of the model, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The connections between computation and geometry in self-assembly make cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper introduces a generalization of regular expressions, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
